WEBVTT

00:00.721 --> 00:03.325
President Conrad Dalton's
inauguration is only one day

00:03.326 --> 00:05.410
away, but he's still
facing a legal challenge

00:05.411 --> 00:07.134
to the legitimacy of his win.

00:07.204 --> 00:08.850
Governor Sam Evans filed a lawsuit

00:08.851 --> 00:10.908
against the state of
Ohio for allowing Dalton

00:10.909 --> 00:11.869
to be put on the ballot,

00:11.870 --> 00:13.707
citing a little known
anti-lobbying law called

00:13.708 --> 00:15.009
the Vasey Act.

00:15.010 --> 00:17.153
Today we've learned the
Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals

00:17.154 --> 00:18.279
has agreed to hear the case.

00:18.280 --> 00:19.781
If the court rules

00:19.782 --> 00:20.849
in Evans' favor,

00:20.850 --> 00:23.184
it could not only revoke
Dalton's presidency,

00:23.185 --> 00:24.853
it could spark a constitutional crisis

00:24.854 --> 00:26.621
that would shake the very foundation

00:26.622 --> 00:28.356
our government was built upon.

00:28.357 --> 00:30.191
What's shaking the very foundation now?

00:30.192 --> 00:32.460
We begin our team coverage in...

00:32.461 --> 00:34.262
The Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals

00:34.263 --> 00:35.563
has agreed to hear Evans' case

00:35.564 --> 00:36.831
against Ohio.

00:36.832 --> 00:39.067
Unbelievable. What are they thinking?

00:39.068 --> 00:42.403
Are they really gonna uphold
some obscure law from 1893?

00:42.404 --> 00:44.138
We'll find out.

00:44.139 --> 00:45.573
Hey,

00:45.574 --> 00:46.608
here's something weird.

00:46.609 --> 00:49.177
I got a call from the CIA.

00:49.178 --> 00:53.681
They want me to come in for
an Ex Post Facto Re-debrief

00:53.682 --> 00:55.450
regarding Black Dog Station.

00:55.451 --> 00:59.153
Well, I was in the CIA for 20 years

00:59.154 --> 01:00.088
and I've never heard of

01:00.089 --> 01:03.358
an Ex Post Facto Re-debrief.

01:03.359 --> 01:04.879
When they shut down the operation down

01:04.881 --> 01:05.984
they called it a "hotwash."

01:05.985 --> 01:09.163
Now they want to get me debriefed.

01:09.164 --> 01:10.765
Why does all their
terminology sound like

01:10.766 --> 01:12.389
something that happens
in a nursing home?

01:13.869 --> 01:15.403
Baby, you okay?

01:15.404 --> 01:17.372
Yeah. Why?

01:17.373 --> 01:20.308
When you get anxious you
take it out on your clothes.

01:24.413 --> 01:27.482
Evans is naming me
specifically in the lawsuit.

01:27.483 --> 01:29.250
He's accusing me

01:29.251 --> 01:33.421
of making overtures to
influence Ohio state senators.

01:33.422 --> 01:35.156
When I did that NFL thing

01:35.157 --> 01:36.157
in Ohio,

01:36.158 --> 01:40.161
I also took some
legislators out to dinner.

01:40.162 --> 01:41.529
Applebee's.

01:41.530 --> 01:43.231
That's where they wanted to go.

01:43.232 --> 01:46.501
I unduly influenced them with
potato skins and hot wings.

01:46.502 --> 01:49.938
Look, I think the only reason
they're hearing the case

01:49.939 --> 01:52.307
is so that Evans can't cry foul.

01:52.308 --> 01:53.608
They're not gonna

01:53.609 --> 01:56.077
upend all of American
politics over this.

01:56.078 --> 01:57.478
Well, either way,

01:57.479 --> 01:59.347
the whole thing is putting a damper

01:59.348 --> 02:00.515
on the inauguration tomorrow.

02:00.516 --> 02:02.083
- Hey, guys.
- Hi.

02:02.084 --> 02:04.686
- Are you cleaning out your closet?
- Maybe.

02:04.687 --> 02:06.788
So this is a good time to talk about

02:06.789 --> 02:08.622
what you're wearing
to the inaugural ball?

02:08.624 --> 02:10.792
As good a time as any, I guess.

02:10.793 --> 02:12.927
A stylist is gonna bring some gowns

02:12.928 --> 02:15.830
to the office and I'm
gonna choose from those.

02:15.831 --> 02:16.898
Really?

02:16.899 --> 02:18.166
Can I come?

02:18.167 --> 02:20.001
You can do better than that.

02:20.002 --> 02:21.269
You can choose for me.

02:21.270 --> 02:22.870
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

02:22.871 --> 02:24.305
Can I also blog about it?

02:24.306 --> 02:25.340
Blog your heart out.

02:25.341 --> 02:26.674
You're the best.

02:26.675 --> 02:28.495
I'll come to your office
right after school.

02:33.748 --> 02:36.616
Okay, my mood is starting
to turn around a little bit.

02:38.820 --> 02:41.222
Hey, you're looking very Wow.

02:41.223 --> 02:43.291
Young DC professional

02:43.292 --> 02:44.759
poised to take over the world,

02:44.760 --> 02:46.694
with just a dash of girlish charm.

02:46.695 --> 02:49.764
Well, that is exactly
what I was going for.

02:49.765 --> 02:51.131
That's right.

02:51.132 --> 02:53.475
It's the first day of your
internship with Russell Jackson.

02:53.476 --> 02:54.335
Are you excited?

02:54.336 --> 02:56.571
With just a dash of terrified.

02:56.572 --> 02:58.906
I still can't believe
he offered me the job.

02:58.907 --> 03:00.508
You saved the guy's
life, I think he felt

03:00.509 --> 03:01.692
it was the least he could do.

03:01.693 --> 03:03.378
He's really scary, though.

03:03.379 --> 03:06.981
Trust me, there is way more bark

03:06.982 --> 03:08.616
than bite with him.

03:08.617 --> 03:10.344
And that was before the heart attack.

03:10.345 --> 03:11.386
I mean, he's just coming back from

03:11.387 --> 03:13.021
a three-week whale-watching cruise.

03:13.022 --> 03:15.063
If that doesn't mellow
you out, nothing can.

03:15.758 --> 03:17.725
Lord.

03:17.726 --> 03:20.395
Inauguration week is
really getting to Blake.

03:20.396 --> 03:24.298
- Bye, guys. - Bye.
- Bye, Dad.

03:24.299 --> 03:25.482
Hi, Blake, everything's good,

03:25.483 --> 03:27.735
I'm just on my way to the office.

03:27.736 --> 03:29.670
Whoa, slow down, slow down, slow down.

03:29.671 --> 03:32.206
Blake, I thought we talked about decaf.

03:32.207 --> 03:34.742
What...

03:34.743 --> 03:36.010
Gifts?

03:38.113 --> 03:39.747
Wow.

03:39.748 --> 03:41.883
You weren't exaggerating.

03:41.884 --> 03:43.217
Yeah.

03:43.218 --> 03:44.519
Sorry for sounding overwhelmed

03:44.520 --> 03:46.621
and possibly even a
little nudgy, it's just

03:46.622 --> 03:49.424
I can't move any of these
until you sign off on them.

03:49.425 --> 03:51.626
Then they have to be processed
by the Protocol Gift Unit

03:51.627 --> 03:52.602
and-and catalogued

03:52.603 --> 03:53.623
by the National Archive.

03:53.624 --> 03:55.727
And there's a room on the
third floor that looks like.

03:55.728 --> 03:56.731
Ali Baba's cave.

03:56.732 --> 03:57.899
It's okay.

03:57.900 --> 03:59.200
We'll get through it together.

03:59.201 --> 04:01.002
No, we won't.

04:01.003 --> 04:02.737
Now I have to go to
the Port of Baltimore

04:02.738 --> 04:04.305
to sign for a gift from.

04:04.306 --> 04:07.375
Byambyn Sendoo, the Mongolian
minister of education.

04:07.376 --> 04:08.743
Why do you have to sign for it?

04:08.744 --> 04:09.777
They wouldn't say.

04:09.778 --> 04:11.679
They were being very Port Authoritarian.

04:11.680 --> 04:15.516
All right, look, you,
go sign for the gift,

04:15.517 --> 04:18.820
and I'll start signing off on these,

04:18.821 --> 04:22.590
and-and we'll just think
of the whole thing as...

04:22.591 --> 04:23.658
an adventure.

04:23.659 --> 04:26.594
Adventures in hell.

04:26.595 --> 04:27.562
I'm sorry.

04:27.563 --> 04:29.106
Madam Secretary, I will course-correct

04:29.107 --> 04:30.698
immediately. You know,

04:30.699 --> 04:31.899
it's good to be the winner.

04:31.900 --> 04:34.335
- These are the spoils of victory.
- Yeah.

04:34.336 --> 04:35.879
I mean, unless the Sixth Circuit Court

04:35.880 --> 04:38.005
finds in favor of Sam Evans.

04:38.006 --> 04:39.373
Then we have to send it all back.

04:41.643 --> 04:42.844
Go.

04:42.845 --> 04:44.545
Drive safe.

04:44.546 --> 04:45.947
- What?
- Just for that,

04:45.948 --> 04:48.081
- you're gonna help me sort.
- Awesome.

04:49.052 --> 04:50.341
Boy.

04:50.342 --> 04:51.919
- What's that?
- It's nothing.

04:51.920 --> 04:53.320
Go, go.

04:55.656 --> 04:57.024
Sort.

04:57.025 --> 04:58.593
What are the categories?

04:59.761 --> 05:01.384
Don't worry about it,
my dad's a hoarder.

05:01.385 --> 05:02.385
I'll figure it out.

05:06.969 --> 05:08.369
Russell.

05:08.370 --> 05:10.271
Welcome back.

05:10.272 --> 05:11.272
How are you feeling?

05:11.273 --> 05:12.907
Top-notch.

05:12.908 --> 05:15.476
So... the cruise was great?

05:15.477 --> 05:17.979
The cruise was excruciating.

05:17.980 --> 05:19.180
Three weeks of watching

05:19.181 --> 05:21.883
what's left of the glaciers float past

05:21.884 --> 05:23.067
and trying to catch a glimpse

05:23.068 --> 05:24.352
of a whale.

05:24.353 --> 05:26.193
Damn leisure time is
gonna kill me a lot faster

05:26.194 --> 05:26.973
than my arteries.

05:26.974 --> 05:28.756
Well, it's nice to have you back.

05:28.757 --> 05:31.959
Jumping right into the fire, no
less, with this Evans debacle.

05:31.960 --> 05:33.943
We thought you might
want to lend a voice

05:33.944 --> 05:35.015
to our strategy session.

05:35.016 --> 05:37.398
Figuring out some way
to derail this lawsuit.

05:37.399 --> 05:41.402
I'm not sure where
there's much room to move.

05:41.403 --> 05:43.437
We can't influence the court.

05:43.438 --> 05:46.407
No, but we can put
them under a spotlight.

05:46.408 --> 05:50.745
Launch a press campaign pointing
out the lack of precedent,

05:50.746 --> 05:53.281
lean hard on the court's obligation

05:53.282 --> 05:54.905
to consider the
stability of the country,

05:54.906 --> 05:56.617
the sanctity of the Electoral College.

05:56.618 --> 05:58.719
Of course, that approach
relies on appealing

05:58.720 --> 06:00.588
to people's higher nature and...

06:00.589 --> 06:02.423
you know how much faith I have in that.

06:02.424 --> 06:04.125
Or we can try to influence Evans.

06:04.126 --> 06:06.260
Who doesn't have a higher
nature to appeal to.

06:06.261 --> 06:08.629
He might be able to
listen to reason, and...

06:08.630 --> 06:11.799
as the aggrieved party, he
can withdraw the complaint.

06:11.800 --> 06:13.534
We can remind him that if he persists,

06:13.535 --> 06:15.570
he won't only be burning
bridges in Washington,

06:15.571 --> 06:18.772
he risks burning down American
democracy in the process.

06:21.609 --> 06:23.110
Okay,

06:23.111 --> 06:26.012
y-you guys are really gonna
make me be the one to say it?

06:27.348 --> 06:28.716
The oppo research.

06:31.186 --> 06:32.720
What happened to being a knight?

06:32.721 --> 06:36.157
The painkillers have worn off.

06:36.158 --> 06:37.592
And they've upped the game.

06:37.593 --> 06:39.976
This is isn't about trying to
influence an election anymore.

06:39.977 --> 06:40.895
Election's over.

06:40.896 --> 06:42.396
This is about dissuading someone

06:42.397 --> 06:44.465
from blatantly abusing the court system

06:44.466 --> 06:46.167
to change the results.

06:46.168 --> 06:47.401
Look,

06:47.402 --> 06:49.737
I-it's not even as dirty as it sounds.

06:49.738 --> 06:52.607
The guy has the gene for
early-onset Alzheimer's

06:52.608 --> 06:54.942
and he didn't disclose
the genetic testing

06:54.943 --> 06:57.078
with the rest of his health report.

06:57.079 --> 07:00.081
Now, who knows, maybe the
voting public wouldn't care.

07:00.082 --> 07:01.981
But they had the right to know.

07:03.684 --> 07:05.686
I can't bring myself to do it, Russell.

07:05.687 --> 07:08.489
We'll just have to let the
chips fall where they may.

07:08.490 --> 07:10.157
What about offering Evans

07:10.158 --> 07:12.126
a position in the White House?

07:12.127 --> 07:13.427
Some sort of advisor.

07:13.428 --> 07:14.996
Maybe even a Cabinet post.

07:14.997 --> 07:18.165
Something prestigious that
we could also live with.

07:18.166 --> 07:22.837
It's unifying and bipartisan.

07:22.838 --> 07:24.438
Who knows, we might even learn something

07:24.462 --> 07:25.473
from his point of view.

07:25.474 --> 07:28.376
Pushed it a little there at the end.

07:28.377 --> 07:31.879
But... there is an argument to be made

07:31.880 --> 07:36.017
for keeping him close by.

07:36.018 --> 07:37.350
It's doable.

07:39.120 --> 07:41.121
Then let's do it.

07:45.459 --> 07:46.794
Abdul-Hafiz Bakkal.

07:46.795 --> 07:48.663
- I've never heard of him.
- Dabir Fakoury?

07:48.664 --> 07:50.898
Dabir Fakoury's an ISIS leader.

07:50.899 --> 07:52.900
Did he ever cross paths
with Hizb Al-Shahid

07:52.901 --> 07:54.702
during your time with Black Dog Station?

07:54.703 --> 07:56.537
Not that I know of.

07:56.538 --> 07:59.840
So you're tracking a connection

07:59.841 --> 08:02.443
between HS and ISIS?

08:02.444 --> 08:03.411
What about Yunis Hamawi?

08:03.412 --> 08:06.614
Also ISIS.

08:06.615 --> 08:08.649
Did his name ever come up?

08:08.650 --> 08:11.185
You guys want to tell
me what this is about?

08:11.186 --> 08:12.553
I might actually be able to help.

08:12.554 --> 08:14.217
So you never found
any concrete connection

08:14.218 --> 08:16.957
between HS and ISIS other
than a shared ideology.

08:16.958 --> 08:18.793
They don't have a shared ideology,

08:18.794 --> 08:20.328
they have a common goal.

08:20.329 --> 08:21.829
A shared ideology would make them

08:21.830 --> 08:23.931
much more dangerous, and, again,

08:23.932 --> 08:25.299
do you want to let me in on that?

08:25.300 --> 08:26.523
We're not authorized to do so,

08:26.524 --> 08:27.835
- Dr. McCord.
- Excuse me,

08:27.836 --> 08:29.870
you're aware of my involvement

08:29.871 --> 08:32.472
in both operations that
effectively dismantled HS,

08:32.474 --> 08:35.809
and yet you're telling me that
my clearance isn't high enough

08:35.811 --> 08:37.745
to be filled in?

08:37.746 --> 08:39.412
That's what we're telling you.

08:40.815 --> 08:43.217
I think we've gotten everything we need.

08:43.217 --> 08:46.354
Thank you for your time.

08:46.355 --> 08:48.700
I'm heading back in
the office now, Blake.

08:48.701 --> 08:49.990
Well, I'm still

08:49.991 --> 08:50.788
at the Port of Baltimore.

08:50.789 --> 08:52.173
I just wanted to let you know that

08:52.174 --> 08:53.774
I am unable to bring the gift home today

08:53.775 --> 08:55.416
because they won't
release it from customs

08:55.417 --> 08:57.102
until it undergoes a
three-day quarantine.

08:57.103 --> 08:58.695
Quarantine? Why?

08:59.464 --> 09:02.100
Because it's a horse.

09:02.101 --> 09:03.168
I'm sorry,

09:03.169 --> 09:04.512
it sounded like you said "horse."

09:04.513 --> 09:05.403
Yes, ma'am.

09:05.404 --> 09:08.540
Minister Sendoo has
sent you a Mongol horse,

09:08.541 --> 09:10.341
it's a...

09:10.342 --> 09:12.544
symbol of national pride and unity.

09:12.545 --> 09:14.445
I have to say, she is gorgeous.

09:14.446 --> 09:15.914
My God.

09:15.915 --> 09:17.148
Send it back.

09:17.149 --> 09:19.751
- Her, and I already signed for her.
- Well, un-sign.

09:19.752 --> 09:21.553
Make it clear that

09:21.554 --> 09:23.288
we are respectfully declining

09:23.289 --> 09:24.789
the gift horse.

09:24.790 --> 09:26.858
May I ask why?

09:26.859 --> 09:30.595
So many reasons, not
the least of which...

09:30.596 --> 09:33.731
we don't have anywhere in the
state department to put her.

09:33.732 --> 09:35.275
I'm sure there's some government-owned

09:35.276 --> 09:36.701
horse property somewhere.

09:36.702 --> 09:37.902
It's not about that.

09:37.903 --> 09:40.838
This is about the
Mongolian referendum vote

09:40.839 --> 09:43.841
to become an autonomous region of China.

09:43.842 --> 09:45.009
Minister Sendoo

09:45.010 --> 09:46.678
favors remaining independent,

09:46.679 --> 09:48.713
and by accepting the horse,

09:48.714 --> 09:51.783
it will signal...

09:51.784 --> 09:54.185
a tacit endorsement of that position.

09:54.186 --> 09:55.753
Because the horse,

09:55.754 --> 09:57.889
symbol of national pride and unity.

09:57.890 --> 09:58.890
See?

09:58.891 --> 10:00.191
Right, right.

10:00.192 --> 10:01.292
That'll make China mad.

10:01.293 --> 10:03.728
And many other Asian nations,

10:03.729 --> 10:05.152
and quite a few Mongolians as well.

10:05.153 --> 10:06.030
Got it.

10:06.031 --> 10:08.333
I will explain the situation

10:08.334 --> 10:10.034
to the Port Authoritarians.

10:10.035 --> 10:11.569
This may take a while.

10:12.671 --> 10:14.038
She's really pretty?

10:14.039 --> 10:15.206
Yes, ma'am.

10:15.207 --> 10:17.375
She's... she's kind
of a cappuccino color,

10:17.376 --> 10:19.177
with a chestnut stripe down her back...

10:19.178 --> 10:20.445
Hanging up now.

10:20.446 --> 10:23.681
Yes, ma'am.

10:23.682 --> 10:24.749
Hi.

10:26.952 --> 10:29.087
"Press the operational
code into the keypad

10:29.088 --> 10:30.855
and hold it down until
you hear the beep."

10:30.856 --> 10:32.490
Yeah, I did that.

10:32.491 --> 10:33.491
How's it going?

10:33.492 --> 10:34.643
Fine, sir.

10:34.644 --> 10:37.028
You can call maintenance if
you're having trouble with that.

10:37.863 --> 10:39.497
I was just about to figure it out.

10:39.498 --> 10:41.881
Adele, will you call maintenance
to program this damn thing?

10:41.882 --> 10:43.915
Yes, sir.

10:44.669 --> 10:48.172
I, I don't like interns.

10:48.173 --> 10:51.542
I never have, I can never find
anything I trust them to do.

10:51.543 --> 10:52.777
- Well...
- Now, I-I...

10:52.778 --> 10:54.178
I'm giving you a chance

10:54.179 --> 10:56.082
- to change my mind.
- I'm honored, Mr. Jackson.

10:56.083 --> 10:57.515
But, there is no bank for good will

10:57.516 --> 10:59.617
around here; You saved
my life, I gave you a job.

10:59.618 --> 11:00.752
- We're even.
- Yes, sir.

11:00.753 --> 11:04.055
Poet Laureate Roland... somebody

11:04.056 --> 11:06.157
is coming in from
Connecticut this afternoon,

11:06.158 --> 11:09.227
he'll be reading a poem at
the inauguration tomorrow.

11:09.228 --> 11:12.697
You can thank JFK for
this enduring legacy

11:12.698 --> 11:15.366
which forces us to stand in
the cold an extra 20 minutes.

11:15.367 --> 11:19.304
Roland Hobbs? I love his work.

11:19.305 --> 11:21.839
I-I actually wrote a paper on
him for my AP English class.

11:21.840 --> 11:23.041
Great. Tell him all about it.

11:23.042 --> 11:25.610
He fancies himself a man of the people,

11:25.611 --> 11:28.112
so he refused to let us
pick him up in a limo.

11:28.113 --> 11:29.981
He was gonna take a
cab from the airport,

11:29.982 --> 11:31.749
but I can't take a chance on losing him,

11:31.750 --> 11:33.584
so he finally agreed to
let us send an intern.

11:33.585 --> 11:35.653
Adele has all the information.

11:35.654 --> 11:39.023
Awesome. That's just so exciting.

11:39.024 --> 11:41.225
Um, thank you. I won't let you down.

11:41.226 --> 11:42.427
Tick tock.

11:44.996 --> 11:48.099
Minister Sendoo, I
am touched and honored

11:48.100 --> 11:51.636
by your generous gift of a Mongol horse.

11:51.637 --> 11:53.304
Unfortunately,

11:53.305 --> 11:56.474
I'm not allowed to
keep diplomatic gifts,

11:56.475 --> 12:00.712
and, well, we just have
no place to put a horse

12:00.713 --> 12:02.980
here in the state department.

12:02.981 --> 12:05.983
I'm very sorry to hear
that, Madam Secretary.

12:05.984 --> 12:09.520
Because we cannot risk
exposing our horse population

12:09.521 --> 12:11.456
to any foreign strains of disease.

12:11.457 --> 12:12.924
If a horse is returned to us

12:12.925 --> 12:16.094
after having been abroad,

12:16.095 --> 12:17.829
it must be euthanized.

12:17.830 --> 12:19.731
You're going to kill her?

12:19.732 --> 12:22.833
Perhaps you would like to reconsider.

